What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The data set contains 84853 loan with 22 columns information like BorrowerAPR, ProsperScore, DebtToIncomeRatio, MonthlyLoanPayment, e.t.c.,

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am interested how employment status will effect loan payments and deliquencies and the factors effect borrower loan status and APR for the loan. how debt to income ration effected.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I think loan payments will be effected by employment status and Monthly Loan Payment and APR will be effected by the loan original amount, monthly income, prosper rating employment status and so on.

color = sb.color_palette()[0]

def draw_barplot(x, y):
    sb.barplot(data=loan, x=x,y=y,color=color)
    plt.ylabel(y)
    plt.xlabel(x)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90);

plt.subplot(2,1,1)
draw_barplot('MonthlyLoanPayment', 'Occupation')


plt.subplot(2,1,2)
draw_barplot('MonthlyLoanPayment','EmploymentStatus')

The top 3 occupations have high monthly loan payment are Judge, Doctor, and Pharmacist. The plot is consistent with salaries of each occupation. we can say this by seeing plot 2 also employed have high monthly loan payment.

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

The borrower APR have negative relationship with loan original amount. It means large amount of loans have low ARP. And also borrower who are employed and self employed paid their monthly loan payment correctly.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶

The amount of deliquents are high for the borrower without proper income. they also have negative correlation, which means less income more amount deliquent.

If the loan amount is large, there is large term. they both have positive correlation. the loan amount for all terms increases with good prosper rating. stated monthly income and credit score have zero correlation. orrower have good credit score with out income and some borrower have good income but they dont have good credit score.The most of the borrowers have AA and HR prosper rating.

Were there any interesting or surprising interactions between features?¶

The surprising element was the relationship between credit score and monthly income.

Conclusions¶

The borrower APR have negative relationship with loan original amount. It means large amount of loans have low ARP. The borrowers with out proper income have more delinquencies and The borrower have employment paid their monthly loan payments on time. Some borrower have good credit score with out income and some borrower have good income but they dont have good credit score.
